editionStmt.edition: This text is an enriched version of the TCP digital transcription A19397 of text S116420 in the English Short Title Catalog (STC 5828). Textual changes and metadata enrichments aim at making the text more computationally tractable, easier to read, and suitable for network-based collaborative curation by amateur and professional end users from many walks of life. The text has been tokenized and linguistically annotated with MorphAdorner. The annotation includes standard spellings that support the display of a text in a standardized format that preserves archaic forms ('loveth', 'seekest'). Textual changes aim at restoring the text the author or stationer meant to publish.

notesStmt.note: In five, or six?, partbooks. At least four of the partbooks each have separate dated title page and register. At head of title, part 1, "Altus."; part 3, "Quintus."; part 4 "Sextus". Part 2, tenor, also has separate dated title page and register, title reads: "Musike of fiue partes.".
Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
